						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up in the village.</p>						

						<p>Kannara (Undated).</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription, referring itself to the reign of Kannara, mentions the authority of a feudatory of the Chellakēta family over Banavasi and records the death of Chaṭṭayya. This record is engraved in characters of about the 9-10th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
